Ticket Management System - Implementation Tasks
Phase 1: Project Setup & Configuration
 Verify Laravel 10.10 installation
 Install required dependencies (Pusher, Laravel WebSockets)
 Configure environment variables
 Create global configuration files
 Set up helper functions
Phase 2: Database Architecture
 Create migrations for all tables (users, tickets, categories, comments, attachments)
 Add indexes and foreign keys
Create database seeders (roles, categories, demo data)
 Create model factories for testing
Phase 3: Models & Relationships
 Create User model with roles
 Create Ticket model with relationships
 Create Category model
 Create Comment model
 Create Attachment model
 Add soft deletes and scopes
Phase 4: Enums & Traits
 Create TicketStatus enum
 Create TicketPriority enum
 Create UserRole enum
 Create reusable traits (HasAttachments, Filterable)
Phase 5: Service Layer
 Create TicketService
 Create CategoryService
 Create NotificationService
 Create FileUploadService
Phase 6: Repository Layer
 Create TicketRepository
 Create CategoryRepository
 Create UserRepository
Phase 7: Form Requests (Backend Validation)
 Create TicketStoreRequest
 Create TicketUpdateRequest
 Create CategoryRequest
 Create CommentRequest
Phase 8: Controllers
 Create DashboardController with real-time stats
 Create TicketController (CRUD + assign + status)
 Create CategoryController (CRUD)
 Create CommentController (AJAX)
 Create AttachmentController (upload/download)
Phase 9: WebSocket Real-time Notifications
 Install and configure Laravel WebSockets / Pusher
 Create notification events (TicketCreated, TicketAssigned, StatusChanged)
 Set up broadcasting channels
 Create notification component for dashboard
Phase 10: Routes & Middleware
 Define web routes with role middleware
 Create RoleMiddleware
 Set up route groups for admin/developer/user
Phase 11: Frontend - Layouts & Components
 Create main layout (app.blade.php)
 Create sidebar navigation
 Create top navbar with notification bell
 Create reusable components (status-badge, priority-badge)
Phase 12: Frontend - Views
 Dashboard view with real-time stats
 Ticket list view (with filters, search, pagination)
 Ticket create/edit forms
 Ticket detail view (with comments)
 Category management view
 User management view
Phase 13: Frontend - JavaScript & Validation
 jQuery form validation
 AJAX ticket status updates
 AJAX comment posting
 Real-time notification listener (WebSocket)
 Toast notifications
 File upload with drag & drop
Phase 14: UI/UX Styling
 Implement responsive design (Bootstrap/Tailwind)
 Style status and priority badges
 Add icons and visual indicators
 Implement dark mode (optional)
 Mobile responsive adjustments
Phase 15: Testing & Optimization
 Test all CRUD operations
 Test real-time notifications
 Verify N+1 query prevention
 Test file uploads
 Performance optimization (caching, eager loading)
Phase 16: Documentation & Deployment
 Create README.md with setup instructions
 Document API endpoints
 Deployment checklist
 Production environment setup